   386‚ÜíPutting all this together, here is a Backus-Naur grammar for ranges,
   387‚Üífor the benefit of parser authors:
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
   408‚Üí## Functions
   410‚ÜíAll methods and classes take a final `options` object argument.  All
   411‚Üíoptions in this object are `false` by default.  The options supported
   412‚Üíare:
   413‚Üí
   414‚Üí- `loose`: Be more forgiving about not-quite-valid semver strings.
   415‚Üí  (Any resulting output will always be 100% strict compliant, of
   416‚Üí  course.)  For backwards compatibility reasons, if the `options`
   417‚Üí  argument is a boolean value instead of an object, it is interpreted
   418‚Üí  to be the `loose` param.
   419‚Üí- `includePrerelease`: Set to suppress the [default
   420‚Üí  behavior](https://github.com/npm/node-semver#prerelease-tags) of
   421‚Üí  excluding prerelease tagged versions from ranges unless they are
   422‚Üí  explicitly opted into.
   423‚Üí
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
   453‚Üí### Comparison
   455‚Üí* `gt(v1, v2)`: `v1 > v2`
   456‚Üí* `gte(v1, v2)`: `v1 >= v2`
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
   478‚Üí### Sorting
   480‚Üí* `sort(versions)`: Returns a sorted array of versions based on the `compareBuild` 
   481‚Üí  function.
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
   485‚Üí### Comparators
   487‚Üí* `intersects(comparator)`: Return true if the comparators intersect
   488‚Üí
   489‚Üí### Ranges
   491‚Üí* `validRange(range)`: Return the valid range or null if it's not valid.
   492‚Üí* `satisfies(version, range)`: Return true if the version satisfies the
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
   531‚Üí### Coercion
   533‚Üí* `coerce(version, options)`: Coerces a string to semver if possible
   534‚Üí
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
   558‚Üí### Clean
   560‚Üí* `clean(version)`: Clean a string to be a valid semver if possible
   561‚Üí
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
